Version three of a game that seems to fill up in less than weeks

Rules
-Everyone should create their own character to do this with
-To do an attack flip a coin (tails is a hit) then roll (depends on weapon) for Damage
-Everyone starts with an inventory space of 7
-depending on the enemy they'll have more or less life eg.
...ant: whereas..soldier(armored):
-Upon Death you arrive in the spirit world and have to find your way back
-The first five members who join will become game masters and create the challenges

Might as well write down your info and story on a word page as not to forget stuff.



Scavenging Rolls (Basic, non event)
-1: 3 spheres of glass
-2: (*Same as 17*)
-3-7: Nothing
-8: 25 gold coins
-9: (*Same as 17*)
-10: A new weapon (roll 1-4) Gun, Sword, Stick, Stave
-11: (*Same as 17*)
-12: You lose 3HP from a bear trap
-13: A diamond (sells for 250 gold coins)
-14: You lose 2 life from a large fall
-15: (*Same as 17*)
-16: You meet up with a magic scroll (abilty: Quick Time; Always go first in a battle
-17:Enemy: (roll 1-4) Spider 4HP, Bandit 7, Kobold Sentinal 5,Light Gunner 6
-18: You find a runic enchantment (+ 1 to any weapon)
-19-20: You discover a maximum life canister (+1 to max life)

No you don't get a checkpoint. You just get a full heal on HP and MP.

Defensive Shield:
Level 1 - Negates all damage for 1 turn. -2
Level 2 - Negates all damage for 2 turns. -2
Level 3 - Negates all damage for 2 turns. After that 10% of the damage that would be taken is reflected on all enemies in the form of spell damage. -3
Level 4 - Negates all damage for 2 turns. After that 20% of the damage that would be taken is reflected on all enemies in the form of spell damage. -3
Level 5 - Negates all damage for 2 turns. After that 30% of the damage that would be taken is reflected on all enemies in the form of spell damage. -4
Level 6 - Negates all damage for 2 turns. After that 40% of the damage that would be taken is reflected on all enemies in the form of spell damage. -4

Cooldown is 5 turns, including the turn you use it.

No you don't get a checkpoint. You just get a full heal on HP and MP.

Defensive Shield:
Level 1 - Negates all damage for 1 turn. -2
Level 2 - Negates all damage for 2 turns. -2
Level 3 - Negates all damage for 2 turns. After that 10% of the damage that would be taken is reflected on all enemies in the form of spell damage. -3
Level 4 - Negates all damage for 2 turns. After that 20% of the damage that would be taken is reflected on all enemies in the form of spell damage. -3
Level 5 - Negates all damage for 2 turns. After that 30% of the damage that would be taken is reflected on all enemies in the form of spell damage. -4
Level 6 - Negates all damage for 2 turns. After that 40% of the damage that would be taken is reflected on all enemies in the form of spell damage. -4

Cooldown is 5 turns, including the turn you use it.

Found it on page 29.
Spell damage without specifying elements would be non-elemental for you.

45424

The "that" in "After that" refers to the 2 turns of the shield effect.

e.g. for level 4 shield:
You shield and attack M1.
M1 attacks you for 3 damage which is blocked off by the shield.
M2 attacks you for 5 damage which is blocked off by the shield.
M3 attacks you but misses.
You attack M1 again but can't kill it.
M1 attacks you for 4 damage which is blocked off by the shield.
M2 attacks you for 1 damage which is blocked off by the shield.
M3 attacks you for 6 damage which is blocked off by the shield.
The shield bursts and deals 3 (rounded off from 3.8 = (3+5+4+1+6)x20%) damage to M1, M2 and M3.

A very good spell, but it takes time to deal damage, which is quite similar to the turret.

The formula:
The wolf gains 1 per level, except:
For every (3n+1)th level starting from level 7, it gains 1 but no .
It gains the Taunt ability at level 4.
Its max damage is increased by 1 every (6n+3)th level.
Its min damage is increased by 1 every (6n)th level.
its mana cost is increased by 1 every (2n+1)th level.

So it costs 6 now.
